Police in Ibadan, Oyo State said yesterday that they arrested five men planning to rob a bank. One of the suspects is an official of a commercial bank, police said. Spokesman of the Command, Adewale Osifeso, in statement said the officers acted on intelligence.   Osinachi’s mum, sister link singer’s death to…     Soldier kills petrol attendant in Minna     I faked my kidnap, says lady   Osifeso said one of the suspects is a contract marketer with a new generation bank, adding that they were apprehended at a hideout in the Agara Odo-Ona area of Akala Expressway in Ibadan. Police said they were planning to rob another new generation bank in the metropolis last Tuesday. “The suspects have all confessed their various involvements in the criminal operations which includes arms procurement and clandestine intelligence gathering ahead of the proposes date of perpetrating the dastardly act,” he said.